< Review>
Staff works well together to help you.  My daughter and I both have dental and orthodontic work done at Waterford.  We originally looked here because of the proximity to home, but even now that we're across town, we still enjoy the office.  The front office works well to find appointments that work with our schedule, and we have both had great results with our orthodontic work.  The front and back office seems to get along well, which is nice.  I've been to other offices where that is not the case, and it feels very awkward to visit.  The staff at Waterford is always friendly and professional, and they seem to have updated technology when it comes to their record keeping and tools.  That gives me more confidence about the work than some outdated offices I've been to in the past.
Waterford also has a points system that offers rewards.  You get points for elected services and even for showing up on time to your appointments.  When you accumulate points, you can get rewarded with perks and gift cards.< /Review>

<Name>Melissa Chu< /Name><time>1578410021402<//time><Rating>4</Rating><Review>I never expected a place like this to be here right next to the ocean, and I think it‚Äôs a brilliant idea. One would usually expect the usual ice cream shop, dessert place, souvenir shop, etc, so this completely opens up a whole new audience to Seaport Village. The tasting room itself is pretty small and cozy, but the service was wonderful. I enjoyed hanging out here. The wines I tried were not bad, but they were nothing too special about them either. The priority here (at Seaport Village) is the ambiance and scenery anyway, right? I can see this as the perfect first stop to a lovely date at Seaport Village.<//Review><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOjxJYAdn9l6EBKr3fwv2tI85qY3It3A7wLiVOe=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOMWlSwfLnS54lPljac3i7xJJYZ3q--rVhHL8i-=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNPExE5-1Is2kY-XQPsS1EFEIw1lQmHx4SkCOJ9=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNZjZrYGAXkvlj6P2XP32lG35D3GwMCMnleo_4n=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMeOWFcsTiw3MVAVgub07A58LHZk1WyySPSgNRx=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM1T6p0CDJXj_PCmRtr3HrF_NIpV3jE1pw7bhpj=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pics><resp>None<//resp><gmapID>0x80dc01ac0f4508d5:0x2897a1e939073dd1</gmapID></record>

1559319088484</Time>
<Rate>4<//Rate>< Text>
First time here with my fiancee' and her sorority sister. The girls wanted to check out a wine spot and this was the closest one that they had from Eddie V's.

A small little quaint tasting room but with a nice patio view of the harbor. Very friendly and knowledgeable service For $20 you get 5 tastings and you get to keep the nice wine glass.

my pallet is more on the tart side. Their whites are okay but the fruit wines are a must try; especially their habanero fruit infused wine double award winner. When in the area i would definitely remember to come back and buy a bottle.</Text>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< text>
Location, location, location.  We were walking/enjoying the sights on Seaport Village with no particular plan or destination.  We were looking around for a good place for a pint, when we spied the San Pasqual Winery.  It has several small tables on it's deck with a fabulous view of the yachts in doc.  The young man behind the counter was personable and knowledgable. He suggested several items and we ended-up spending over an hour sipping wine and watching the world go by.  If your looking to relax and drink a wide variety of wine in Seaport Village, this is the place!< /text>

<user_id>118424610454496906629< /user_id><name>Manda W.< /name><Date>1484149619581</Date>< rating>
5< /rating>
<Text>What a cool place, especially for not even knowing there was any sort of a town on the CA side of the lake. The campground is pretty typical, and we were glad to have gotten a spot with some shade trees. The laundry worked well, but we didn't use the restrooms, so I don't have a comment for those. We were there on Thanksgiving weekend, and they hosted a huge bonfire with live music for all, that was free! Everything you need is within walking distance, groceries, casino, a couple of restaurants/bars (one at the casino), hardware store, (add to that the gas station, and that's pretty much the whole town). The casino has a ferry boat to the AZ side of the lake, and when we were here it was only $2 round trip! Can't beat that!<//Text>< pictures>
None<//pictures>

<Review>My first appointment with this clinic was great. The doctor I saw was kind and understanding. I have chronic migraines and she said they would be able to continue my treatments, rather than me having to see a specialist for something routine. I set an appointment for the following week, knowing we may have to reschedule due to insurance authorizations. This is where I began to encounter problems. The front office staff and authorization department have proved to be incredibly difficult to work with or get results from. The authorization department failed to answer a question from my insurance company and the request was denied. The office did not inform me of this, in fact I had to call the office every other day for a week and a half before getting an answer. The following week after speaking with my insurance company I informed the office how to obtain authorization, they did and asked me to follow up with the pharmacy. The pharmacy never received the prescription, so I again tried to call the office staff and was unable to get through. I finally spoke to someone two days later to cancel my appointment for the second time since without the prescription, the doctor would be unable to perform the procedure. It has now been one week since the last message I left and I have not received a callback. I was finally able to get information once I broke down sobbing to Rich in the scheduling department. I was so frustrated with not knowing any information regarding a procedure for my healthcare. It turned out they had sent the pharmacy the prescription using information I had provided, but had not written the prescription correctly so again my insurance company was denying to fill the prescription. By this time I had began the process to switch insurance carriers and since they had taken a month to unsuccessfully get a procedure authorized and completed it was too late and my insurance had switched.  The office is almost  impossible to get in touch with the touch option for the front rings on a continuous message loop and the option for the operator forces you to leave a message after two minutes of hold time and if you do leave a message do not expect a call back. Turns out it will be easier for me to fly to southern California every 3 months than deal with this office. If you only need to see them for the most basic medical care maybe they're great, if you need anything requiring additional effort on the office's part or if you need to speak to an actual person regarding your healthcare I would highly suggest finding a different office.< /Review>< Rating>

At one time I would come in here several times a week to get bagels.  The food was fine. There was a woman working there, a manager, who was always extremely rude to her employees. At first I thought it was a cultural (asian) thing, as certain cultures can appear to be rude from an American perspective. But after coming here for a while I realized that it was in fact not a cultural thing. Her only mode of communication was yelling and scolding over the smallest issues. Instead of politely asking an employee to do something, she would yell at them to do it. She did this in front of customers. She completely terrorized her employees. I saw numerous new employees come and go. At one point I saw a girl on her first day on the verge of crying. I have no doubt many of their employees quit after their first shift. What is there to say about AV Chevy other than what a wonderful group of sales, service and accounts people! Truly A-Star service in every way. These guys sold me an amazing car (2019 Mustang GT Convertible) at one of the best prices I've seen and took care of me throughout the entire process, including some issues I had after purchase.

The car had an issue with the window alignment on both sides and, despite being overdue on its warrantee, the gang at AV Chevy got it fixed for me, paid for the work, gave me a loaner car and didn't even charge me when I forgot to bring it back gassed up (I REALLY FORGOT)!

My sales rep, Aga, has been so lovely and is always professional. She never seems frustrated even when she's done her job and sold the vehicle. She always got back to me in a timely manner and updated me like she promised she would.

My service rep, Luis, was super helpful and accommodating and got things done quickly for me. He also reached out when the car was good to go and gave me an update.

The manager was awesome throughout all of this. The finance rep was fantastic and the people on the front desk are super friendly and professional. These guys don't mess around on service!

I will return to AV Chevy if I ever fall out of love with my GT and want a new car. I highly recommend these guys if you want a group of people who won't let you leave until you're satisfied.<//review>

<Name>Madison Anderson</Name><Time>1608513203397<//Time><Rating>1<//Rating>< Review>
Horrible service. Absolutely horrible.

My car went into AV Chevy's service department the first week of October and is still there as we I write this (9+ weeks later).

Since the day my car was dropped off I have received TERRIBLE customer service. I have not ONCE received an update without having to call AND text 2, 3, 4 + times, sometimes even multiple days apart (trying to be understanding of busy schedules I'd try to give them time to respond). Even one of the managers continued to not return my calls.

Besides being TERRIBLE at communicating, they also are extremely unhelpful in other areas. My new (bought used) car is there due to needing a new transmission (thankfully I bought the extended warranty) and due to no fault of my own. Warranty only covered 5 days of a rental and knowing this within the first week of my car being there I immediately looked for assistance from multiple employees at chevy. I tried everything to get assistance because I genuinely needed it and was told they could do NOTHING for me everywhere I looked. Fast forward a couple weeks and I exhausted every option of borrowing cars and rides before I HAD to rent a car, and it wasn't until I got ahold of a manager and explained my dissatisfaction with everything that they FINALLY offered to help with half of the rental (which I was originally told was impossible due to their policies). Well 26 days later of being in a rental, I could no longer afford my half. I called once again pleading for help, and they again had continued to REFUSE to help with more than half of my rental fees; even though I in depth explained how I could not afford even half. So, regardless of badly needing a vehicle, I was forced to return the rental. (According to them they would of continued to cover half of the cost, for any length of time, regardless of the price "as long as I was covering the other half". So you'll pay $2000 if needed, as long as I match the $2000, but you can't just cover the $1000? Does this make ANY sense? No, not to me either.)

Well due to me having to return my rental I've been late to work, have had to leave early, had to call out and miss out on 3 whole work days and caused a lot of issues at my place(s) of work (beings that I myself am a manager and am scheduled to work 6 days a week). So this WHOLE situation has caused me a load of stress and A LOT of money. Even explaining everything, still there was "nothing they could do".

Well, now 9 weeks later my new transmission was installed and programmed, but couldn't be released because now it had another broken part. Oh, and I got this update after 3 days of calling to see what was going on with my car and getting no straight answer (again, not once receiving an update without looking for one). I again was told my car needed to stay longer, this time for a separate repair and was told  again there was nothing they could do about a rental. I then got in contact with Steve, the head manager, and was told he was "just brought into this case" (9 weeks later after me asking to speak to a manager multiple times?). Well after a LOOONNNGG conversation and some begging and pleading he got me into a rental from them free of charge until my car is finished.

I am thankful of the help I received after 9 weeks of hell, but what about the maxed out credit card I have that should have NEVER been my concern? What about the missed days at work (hundreds of dollars)? What about hearing that "there was nothing they could do for me rental wise because they don't have loaner cars and policies state they can't do anything" yet now that THEY'RE responsible for my car needing repairs NOW rules change?

UPDATE: Still have not heard from a manager in regards to my experience regardless of their comment on the post. Ontop of that, when I finally did get my car back the gas tank was almost on E (even though I dropped it off at a 1/4) and my experience continued to be unpleasant. Terrible, terrible service. I'll be reaching out to the head of Chevy to dispute all of this.< /Review>

<gmap_id>0x80c25afbe425eae5:0xf85f5bd071e6c797<//gmap_id><date>1607802710108<//date>< Text>
My and my husband's purchase experience was very messy and disorganized. We came pre-qualified and with a trade-in vehicle, fully prepared with more paperwork than was even needed. Our sales experience began with the salesman not having much knowledge of the vehicle we planned to purchase (we had to Google certain vehicle specifications and certain features were incorrectly explained, which we found out later). Next, we were offered a trade-in value below KBB and financing options that were significantly different than what we came pre-approved for. In addition, we were informed that our trade-in vehicle was leaking what was possibly coolant and our check engine light was on. When we expressed concern over this (because our last vehicle service was flushing/replacing coolant barely two months prior at AV Chevy and we had no issues prior to our arrival), our salesman seemed to lose his friendly demeanor and dismissed our concerns. However, we went ahead as planned and focused on the purchase of a new vehicle. We were upfront with our salesman that we wanted to finance with the company that pre-approved us and we did not want any other hard inquiries to our credit from them attempting financing with other companies. After some time negotiating, he informed us that the finance department recommended applying with another lender for a significantly lower rate, so we agreed to one additional hard inquiry. Our salesman came back with the numbers, which were agreeable to us, so we accepted the terms and proceeded to wait for the financing department to be ready with our paperwork. After the better part of another hour, financing was finally ready with the paperwork. As we were completing the paperwork, the finance representative explained our lender would be the company with whom we came pre-qualified. We explained that this was incorrect, as our salesman had us agree to an additional application with another lender that offered us a lower rate and monthly payment. The finance representative then went through all of the application information again, only to inform us that our original lender was the correct one and the lender from the second inquiry would result in a higher interest rate and payment. When the process was finally finished, my husband had to ask no less than four times to have a bow placed on the vehicle for pictures. Our salesman even went so far as to solicit a good review by telling us that his pay would be affected for the next six months if he received less than perfect remarks. We did not appreciate the guilt trip. We spent five long hours at AV Chevy haggling over prices, checking the dealerships details, and waiting for each next step of the process to be completed, only to be left with THREE hard inquiries on our credit for the next two years (we have no idea why they ran our credit a third time), more miscommunications than we could count, and no intention of using AV Chevy again. Ultimately, we are only giving one star for the fact that we love our new vehicle and have already received numerous compliments on it. We will be heading to the next nearest Chevy dealership for standard maintenance and only going to AV Chevy out of sheer necessity if we cannot get our vehicle anywhere else.< /Text>

<Review>I CAUGHT ANTELOPE VALLEY FLAT OUT LYING TO ME - DO NOT GO HERE OR BUY ANY VEHICLE PRODUCED BY GM PERIOD - Go across the street and buy a Toyota!

I have a 2016 Colorado Z71 that was taken to Antelope Valley 5-6 times within 6,000 miles for several major issues (stuck in 4wd, clunking suspension, transmission "chuggle", hard start/misfire, blown speaker, bad infotainment module, bad AC compressor, bad drivers window motor/regulator). To be fair, the truck was not purchased in Kansas not at Antelope Valley.

Over the course of these visits Antelope Valley could not reproduce the "chuggle", hard starting, or being stuck in 4wd which I more or less expected. These problems only happen about once a week, but they have still caused the truck to be towed at one point or another. The speaker, window motor, and AC compressor were eventually replaced and I was told the infotainment module and the rear leaf springs/shackles were "backordered" so I waited a week and called back. Still "backordered". The next week: still backordered. the week after that: still backordered. Half of the time I couldn't even get ahold of the service department and had to leave a message with the receptionist - which probably didn't actually make it to the service department.

I called GM directly twice after the 3rd or 4th dealer visit but was not able to get ahold of anyone to find out if the parts were actually backordered or not. Every time I would take my truck in for a new problem it would sit at the dealer for several days before they diagnosed the problem. The extended warranty that was sold to me by Chevrolet went from covering my rental car completely when I dropped the truck off, to only covering 1 day because technically the dealer only used half a day to diagnose the truck and it sat the rest of the time it was at the dealer, to not covering any of the rental at all while my truck was in the shop because on the day Antelope Valley did work on it, they only charged 3 work hours and the rental is only covered if they work on it for at least half a day (4 hours).

At this point I am already extremely frustrated with the truck and the dealer experience as a whole to the point that I am shopping for a Tacoma to trade for my Colorado less than 6 months after purchasing it and reaching out to lawyers to see if I have a Lemon Law case. I called Rally Buick GMC Cadillac to see if they could get the parts (I had the exact part numbers that were "backordered" from Antelope Valley). Sure enough, there are 10, 20, 30 of each part that I needed available at the only local GM parts warehouse. So Antelope Valley was flat out LYING to me about the parts being backordered. I have all receipts from Antelope Valley and planned to get a receipt from Rally after they fixed the truck stating that the parts were in fact available when Antelope Valley said they were not. I have everything together to confront the owner of Antelope Valley, but unfortunately my truck was totaled 5 days before my appointment at Rally to finally get it fixed. Its not worth pursuing since I (thankfully) don't even have the truck, I just hope someone reads this review and decides not to give their business to these jokers. I have filed complaints with the Better Business Bureau and GM Directly. According to the GM rep this is not the first complaint for this exact problem from this dealer.

Before this truck I drove older (1995-2010) GM products almost exclusively and loved all of them, but I will not be buying ANY vehicle produced by GM for a very long time after the experience I have had over the last 6 months or so. Pay the extra few thousand to buy a Honda or a Toyota; its well worth it to keep your sanity< /Review>< Pics>

<review>I'm writing to review my experience buying a Chevy Bolt. The staff was very friendly and candid. Paul H. helped project an image of trust and honesty. In finance, Rhonda was personable, a quick worker, and also nice. In the purchasing process I was able to keep in frequent contact with Rhonda which helps avoid surprises and misunderstandings. That's the good, but there are opportunities for improvement: Some of the Chevrolet materials had errors. For instance, the Bolt materials indicated need for an oil change, which is not true. I would appreciate more up front information on recommended service schedules for the Bolt and Volt(and maybe all cars?). I had to ask and the staff had to dig up the information. The more transparency, the better the dealership experience. In addition, the dealership sent me home without the charging cable; I noticed and was able to get one without hassle immediately, but this could have been a big issue considering the car had not been charged and was delivered with about 15% battery capacity. The dealership talked me into an option contract to take the car immediately. It was not well-communicated what the option contract was, and what the time lines were, and what it would mean to me in different financial scenarios. I would say this feels a little bit like the dealership setting a trap for me and adds to the negative perception people have towards dealerships. <review>We have been with this dealership since they opened. In fact, we have been with the owners of this dealership since 1997, as Saturn of the AV.
Your experience, here, can be great. Every experience is what you make it.
Some of the reviews on Yelp aren't the best. To those people I say, do your homework on how to buy a car. Everyone will run a credit check. They don't want to sell you a car you can't afford. They want you to drive away happy and not burdened. AV Chevy will get you the best possible interest rate , even if your credit is not the best.
We have leased, bought and most recently, special ordered our latest vehicle, a Chevy Colorado diesel.
Only once in all that time did we ever have a bad word to say about anyone. That one person was soon after let go.
Go in with a listening ear and learn. Everyone is prepared to help you have a good experience. If you go in with a know-it-all attitude or you're not satisfied with your sales or service rep, ask for someone else. Buying a vehicle or having your vehicle serviced is like a marriage, all of us work well with certain personality types better than others.
Like I said, we're totally satisfied. That's why we've gone back time after time.
As far as servicing goes, if they say that your vehicle needs something or it can wait for another 5,000 miles, do what they say. It will cost you less in the long run. If you can put that new alternator in yourself, do it, otherwise quit complaining when it gives out. They really don't want to say I told you so.
Satisfied in Palmdale!< /review>< Pictures>

< text>
Our check engine light came on after climbing the Tehachapi Pass,in early October 2018 while pulling a fifth wheel with our 2006 2500HD Chevy Silverado.  We were able to drive into Lancaster, CA to Antelope Valley Chevrolet who said they could fit us in and were able to shuttle us to the fairgrounds where we had left our RV. The service department determined that we needed two sensors replaced on our vehicle, a turbo sensor and a cam shaft sensor. Even though their communication was lacking after about five days (a weekend didn't help) they were able to get us back on the road. We returned home to Oregon with the truck working fine. Then in mid November we experienced trouble with the truck intermittently refusing to start. After being towed to our local Chevrolet dealer twice, they were finally able to determine that the Cam shaft sensor which Antelope Valley Chevrolet had installed for us, was installed incorrectly leading to corrosion and a short. The technician at AV Chevrolet had left off a seal/gasket causing the corrosion. In early December once the truck was repaired, we contacted Nicole the service manager asking for help with the $518 in repair costs we incurred due to their error. She told us to send pictures of the part, invoices, etc. and told us she would talk with the general manager and get back to us. In mid January after not hearing back from Nicole, we emailed again and received no response. At the end of January we emailed the general manager with all of our information and once again received no reply. We gave them every opportunity to help make this right and basically they blew us off. I would not recommend this dealership to any one for service of their vehicle unless they have no other options available. Our local dealership Suburban Chevrolet in Sandy, OR is fantastic and would never treat a customer like this. Even if they could not help financially, they would at least take the time to discuss the problem and try to come up with some solution. We have also dealt with Chevrolet dealerships in Crescent City, CA and Fresno, CA who were also fantastic and provided the service we have come to expect from Chevrolet dealerships. I have also contacted Chevrolet to let them know that their Antelope Valley Chevrolet Service Department does not live up to the quality and service that should be expected from a Chevrolet dealer.

I tried to give no stars as that is what they deserve, but I cannot post this review without giving at least one star.<//text>
